{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "The effects obtained in the ABCD model are more pronounced for τ, namely for low q 2 the observable P ′ 5 can differ from SM.",
    "For B s → ϕµ -µ +, using the form factors in [76] with parameters in Table 3, we find in SM: B(B s → ϕµ -µ +) = (11.8 ± 2.3) × 10 -7 (|λ *ts |/0.04) 2, confirming that a higher value is foreseen for this rate with respect to the measured B(B s → ϕµ -µ +) exp = (8.4 ± 0.4) × 10 -7 [30].",
    "Measurements are not available for the τ mode: we find B(B s → ϕτ -τ +) = (1.02 ± 0.20) × 10 -7 (|λ * ts |/0.04) 2 in SM.",
    "Fig. 13 shows the correlation between the two LFC decays in the ABCD model: the plot for M Z ′ = 1 TeV shows that the range for the τ mode is B(B s → ϕτ -τ +) = (0.9±0.25)×10 -7, for M Z ′ = 3 TeV the range is B(B s → ϕτ -τ +) = (0.9±0.2)×10 -7.",
    "However, since B(B s → ϕµ -µ +) exp is not reproduced, a puzzle remains unsolved for this mode."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "For B s → ϕµ -µ +, using the form factors in [76] with parameters in Table 3, we find in SM: B(B s → ϕµ -µ +) = (11.8 ± 2.3) × 10 -7 (|λ *ts |/0.04) 2, confirming that a higher value is foreseen for this rate with respect to the measured B(B s → ϕµ -µ +) exp = (8.4 ± 0.4) × 10 -7 [30]."
  ]
}